So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In India, the mental illness known in the West as [Anomie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anomie) is cured with the drugs Soma, Amrita, and Ganja plus \\(in a more modern interpretation\\) Peyote and Ayahuasca.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prohibition of drugs at no time endangers the personal autonomy of the individual.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, the potency of available alcoholic drinks grew significantly \\([pg. 3](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization might lead to increased consumption among children.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One can imagine that an inebriated cannabis user may leave the house less often and therefore spend less money. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education and information might not be enough to ensure thoughtful drug use.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The human right to personal autonomy](http://www.corteidh.or.cr/tablas/r26750.pdf) should include the freedom to take drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugging and raping someone is way more risky than buying illegal drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research chemicals, which are used as [date rape drugs](https://drugabuse.com/date-rape-drugs/), are constantly evolving and changing formulations to escape existing regulation. It is unlikely that the law would be able to control all of them. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'No alcohol or tobacco company has openly killed anyone to continue selling their product.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As this is also true under prohibition, it's an argument for proper education, not an argument against legalization. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Controlled substances, while controlled, are still obtained through the black market. Whether it is a date-rape drug or marijuana, legislation still cannot control whether illegal drugs are illegally obtained. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "They already do this with alcohol or cigarettes, which hasn't caused our society to collapse."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legalised, people who are addicted may feel more comfortable seeking help and support as they won't be viewed as criminals in the way they currently are. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Research suggests that [two-thirds](https://www.verywell.com/domestic-abuse-and-alcohol-62643) of incidents of domestic violence happen while the perpetrator is under the influence of alcohol.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Cocaine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_harmfulness#/media/File:HarmCausedByDrugsTable.svg) is less harmful than alcohol, and only slightly more addictive. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Economic hardship resulting from drug use would be better addressed by spending money on treatment, rather than attempting to control supply. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are still many other ways in which criminal associations could take advantage of the situation and legally start selling drugs or exploiting the farmers as they do now.'}
